3.6 Exploratory Data Analysis
Exploratory Data Analysis is the process of understanding and analyzing data before building a model.
It is used to find patterns, trends, missing values, and errors in the dataset.
In Crop Recommendation System, EDA helps to:
Understand soil and weather data
Identify missing or incorrect values
Analyze relationships between crops and soil nutrients
Visualize data using graphs and charts

