Chapter 4- Implementation details
Date- 29/09/2025 to 18/10/25
### **Modules of Crop Recommendation System**

1. Data Collection Module
   Collects soil data, weather data, and crop details.
2. Data Preprocessing Module
   Cleans data by removing errors, handling missing values, and normalizing data.
3. Exploratory Data Analysis Module
   Analyzes and visualizes data to understand patterns and relationships.
4. Model Training Module
   Applies machine learning algorithms to train the crop prediction model.
5. Crop Recommendation Module
   Predicts and recommends the most suitable crop for given inputs.
6. Result Display Module
   Shows the recommended crop and related information to the user.
Chapter 5 - Results
Date- 27/10/25 to 04/11/25

5.1 Results
The Crop Recommendation System successfully predicts the most suitable crop
based on soil nutrients and weather conditions.
It helps farmers make accurate crop selection, 
reduces crop failure, and improves yield and productivity.
The system provides quick and reliable recommendations,
supporting smart and sustainable agriculture.

5.2 Performance Metrics
### **Performance Metrics of Crop Recommendation System**

To evaluate how well the system predicts the suitable crop, the following metrics are used:

1. Accuracy
   Measures the percentage of correct crop predictions out of total predictions.

2. Precision
   Indicates how many of the recommended crops were actually suitable.

3. Recall (Sensitivity)
   Measures how many suitable crops were correctly identified by the system.

4. F1-Score
   Combines precision and recall to give a single performance score.

5. Confusion Matrix
   Shows correct and incorrect predictions for each crop class.

6. Mean Absolute Error 
   Measures the average difference between predicted and actual crop suitability scores.

5.3 Model Evaluation
Split data into training and testing sets

Train the model using algorithms like Decision Tree or Random Forest

Predict crops on testing data

Compare predictions with actual crops

Check accuracy, precision, recall, F1-score

Select the best-performing model

Chapter 6 - Conclusion

The Crop Recommendation System helps farmers choose the right crop based on soil, 
weather, and other environmental factors. It improves crop yield, reduces losses, and supports 
sustainable farming. By using data analysis and machine learning, the system provides accurate, 
fast, and reliable recommendations, making farming more efficient and profitable.

